results.name: Number of proper divisors of n of the form 6*k + 5.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..65537
formula: a(n) = A319995(n) - [+5 = n (mod 6)], where [ ] is the Iverson bracket, giving 1 only when n = -1 mod 6, and 0 otherwise.
G.f.: Sum_{k>=1} x^(12*k-2) / (1 - x^(6*k-1)). - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Apr 14 2021
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Oct 03 2018
